      "content": "I see what you mean about the \"old-money\" aspect. But wouldn't someone looking for luxury also be interested in cultural depth? \n\nIn your experience writing for luxury brands, why is \"multiculturalism\" or \"ethnic architecture\" (like in B or C) seen as less \"prestigious\" than something like colonial architecture? Is there a specific reason why those elements don't translate well to a high-end audience?",
